document_data.name: Iku-In
document_data.mainbody: '''Iku-In''' was a structure located in the heart of the city of [[Semmishi]] in [[Wa]].
document_data.History:
Iku-In was originally constructed as a memorial shrine, dedicated to lives lost in a great fire that occurred in {{YearlinkConvert|1674|WY}}.

Over time, as Semmishi became a city of vice, Iku-In fell into disrepair. By {{YearlinkConvert|1775|WY}}, the structure was being used to host wrestling matches.
